author: wn.com
title: Funding decision for dangerous U.S. 35 intersections could come soon
text: A proposed $120 million construction project to replace dangerous intersections on U.S. 35 in Beavercreek could get a lift by the end of the year if state highway officials approve funding. Greene County officials last week attended a Ohio Department of Transportation Review Advisory Council public hearing in Columbus to urge the state transportation agency for $32 million to move forward with plans for right-of-way acquisition, engineering and construction.
